			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Roles &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>
<p>
The Travel Consultant will report to the Travel Duty Manager who will be responsible for: Selling of travel packages, flight tickets, travel insurance, ferry tickets, hotel accommodation, tours and ferry tickets. Duties include confirming reservation, answering walk-in/phone enquiries, preparation of customer invoices, promoting&nbsp;destinations, tour packages and other services, provide customers with travel recommendation and planning of travel itineraries.</p>
<p>
Travel Consultant will have to be flexible to work under long hours (or shift duties) with tight timelines and be able to adapt to changes in order to meet clients&#39; requests.</p>
<p>
The Travel Consultant must be presentable, fluent in English &amp; Chinese, comfortable with sales, possess a good working knowledge of Microsoft office, comfortable with social networking sites, be confident and have a strong eye for detail.</p>
]]></description>
